<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                        <head>No. 140.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoffman</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-06-06"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 6, 1876</date>.
                                (Received June 6.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Read 887. Left copy with Lord Derby to-day. Sent him copy of 890. Brent
                            applies for <hi rend="italic">habeas corpus</hi>. British government
                            will ask remand until fifteenth.</p>
                        <closer><signed>HOFFMAN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>